1. Static methos can access only static variables or other static methods of the class.
2. Static methods belog to a class and they can be accessed using objects or directly by class name
3. this and super keywords cannot be used in static context.

Static blocks:
1. static blocks can only access static variables and methods.
2. Static blocks cacn be used to initialize variables
3. Once the class get's loaded, the static blocks gets executed first, in the order in which they are written.